(22502, 1, '2016-06-14 13:50:02', '2016-06-14 18:50:02', '[vc_row css=".vc_custom_1466171912888{padding-right: 2em !important;padding-left: 2em !important;}"][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_column_text]The natural latex, also known as vegetable leather, for its resemblance to leather, is a rubber latex blanket with cotton. It is achieved by extracting shiringa latex trees, mixed with natural colorants and then smearing it on canvas streched cotton or steam drying. Is an ancient technique where trees aren´t cut down, only it removed the necesary latex for the tree to continue living and regenerated\r\n\r\nThe shiringa is a tree that grows up exclusive in the Amazon and it has inside a milky liquid call latex, when it is extracted and through artesanal proccess it has converted in latex and cotton blankets that is very similar to leather. Also call vegetable leather.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h4><strong>"It is a very old technique where trees are not cut down, but the latex is extracted just enough for the tree alive and continue to regenerate".</strong></h4>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_single_image image="22464" img_size="large" alignment="center"][vc_single_image image="22646" img_size="large" alignment="center"][vc_single_image image="22647" img_size="large" alignment="center"][vc_single_image image="22648" img_size="large" alignment="center"][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'What is the vegetable leather?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'what-is-the-vegetable-leather', '', '', '2016-06-17 08:59:40', '2016-06-17 13:59:40', '', 22509, 'http://localhost/evea/?page_id=22502', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(22503, 1, '2016-06-14 13:50:02', '2016-06-14 18:50:02', 'Natural latex, also known as vegetable leather, for its resemblance to leather, is a blanket of rubber latex with cotton fabric. It is achieved by extracting latex Shiringa trees, mixed with natural dyes and then smearing it on canvas stretched cotton or steam drying. It is a very old technique where trees are not cut down, but the latex just enough for the tree to continue with life and regenerate is extracted.\r\n\r\nShiringa is a tree that grows exclusively in the Amazon and has inside a milky liquid called latex, which to be extracted and using a traditional process, is converted into blankets latex and cotton, which has a leather-like. also called vegetable leather.', 'WHAT IS NATURAL LATEX LEATHER OR VEGETABLE?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '22502-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-14 13:50:02', '2016-06-14 18:50:02', '', 22502, 'http://localhost/evea/blog/2016/06/14/22502-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(22504, 1, '2016-06-14 13:50:50', '2016-06-14 18:50:50', 'Natural latex, also known as vegetable leather, for its resemblance to leather, is a blanket of rubber latex with cotton fabric. It is achieved by extracting latex Shiringa trees, mixed with natural dyes and then smearing it on canvas stretched cotton or steam drying. It is a very old technique where trees are not cut down, but the latex just enough for the tree to continue with life and regenerate is extracted.\r\n\r\nShiringa is a tree that grows exclusively in the Amazon and has inside a milky liquid called latex, which to be extracted and using a traditional process, is converted into blankets latex and cotton, which has a leather-like. also called vegetable leather.', 'What is natural latex leather or vegetable?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '22502-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-14 13:50:50', '2016-06-14 18:50:50', '', 22502, 'http://localhost/evea/blog/2016/06/14/22502-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(22505, 1, '2016-06-14 13:51:57', '2016-06-14 18:51:57', '[vc_row css=".vc_custom_1466172663103{padding-right: 2em !important;padding-left: 2em !important;}"][vc_column width="2/3" css=".vc_custom_1466172602845{padding-right: 2em !important;padding-left: 2em !important;}"][vc_column_text]We know that ilegal and indiscriminate logging is the big problem of the Amazon. A year more than 150000 hectares of forest are deforested, either by illegal loggers, drug trafficking , etc. “ Amazon deforestation can alter the climate of the whole continent, rainfall patterns and cause serious droughts in some regions… If South America has the climate and the ecosystem it has, it is thanks to the Amazon…” (words Brazilian scientist Antonio Nobre)\r\n\r\nEvea Ecofashion, aware of this problem and valuable product that made these families and entrepreneurial communities, working with them to create clothing accesories such as wallets, handbags, bags, an others, offering an enviromentally friendly alternative in harmony with nature. In wich each bag developed by 2 or 3 trees are preserved, since each community has for use and protection , between 80 and 150 trees, covering an area of 300 hectares of preserved forest only for one family. Try to imagine if we can work with hundred of families.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h4><strong>"Amazon deforestation can alter the climate of the whole continent, rainfall patterns and cause severe droughts".</strong></h4>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_single_image image="22658" img_size="large" alignment="center"][vc_single_image image="22659" img_size="large" alignment="center"][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Amazon forest conservation', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'amazon_forest_conservation', '', '', '2016-06-17 09:13:45', '2016-06-17 14:13:45', '', 22509, 'http://localhost/evea/?page_id=22505', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(22506, 1, '2016-06-14 13:51:57', '2016-06-14 18:51:57', 'Sabemos que la tala ilegal e indiscriminada es el gran problema de la Amazonía. Al año se deforestan más de 150 000 hectáreas de bosque, ya sea por madereros ilegales, por narcotráfico, etc. “La deforestación del Amazonas puede alterar el clima de todo el continente, los patrones de lluvia, y provocar graves sequías en algunas regiones…. Si América del Sur tiene el clima y el ecosistema que tiene, es gracias a la Amazonía…”\r\n\r\nEvea Ecofashion, conciente de este problema y del valioso producto que elaboran estas familias y comunidades emprendedoras, trabaja con ellas para crear accesorios de vestir como carteras y bolsos, ofreciendo una alternativa ecológica en armonía con la naturaleza. En la cual por cada cartera elaborada se conservan 3 árboles de caucho, ya que cada comunero posee para su uso y protección, entre 80 a 150 árboles, que cubren un área aproximada de 300 hectáreas de bosque conservado.', 'Forest conservation of the Amazon', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '22505-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-14 13:51:57', '2016-06-14 18:51:57', '', 22505, 'http://localhost/evea/blog/2016/06/14/22505-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(22507, 1, '2016-06-14 13:53:16', '2016-06-14 18:53:16', '[vc_row css=".vc_custom_1466173057361{padding-right: 2em !important;padding-left: 2em !important;}"][vc_column][vc_column_text]One of the Evea Ecofashion objetives is to promote ethical consumption of resposibly produced products for the Amazonian communities. Imagine the impact generated by products of the textile industry, not just for the chemicals and environmental pollution, if not the social impact of the abuse, explotation and unfair trade. Evea promotes awareness, creating jobs, ensuring decent living conditions; to preserve the balance of ecosystems and to improve the income level of all participating cycle design, production and packaging of the product, fighting, thus social exclusion and environmental damage.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_single_image image="22662" img_size="large" alignment="center"][vc_single_image image="22663" img_size="large" alignment="center"][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Ethical and responsible consumption', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'ethical-and-responsible-consumption', '', '', '2016-06-17 09:17:42', '2016-06-17 14:17:42', '', 22509, 'http://localhost/evea/?page_id=22507', 0, 'page', '', 0),
