(22511, 1, '2016-06-14 13:56:04', '2016-06-14 18:56:04', '[vc_row css=".vc_custom_1466172495999{padding-right: 2em !important;padding-left: 2em !important;}"][vc_column][vc_column_text]Evea Ecofashion works with families Amazonian Peru based on the fair trade system, in a responsible, ethical and transparent, looking for the development of collecting and vegetable leather producing communities. Families articulate an integrated work, where tradition is passed down from father to son, involvement of the whole family where women contribute to the development of vegetable leather rugs.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_single_image image="22651" img_size="large" alignment="center"][vc_single_image image="22653" img_size="large" alignment="center"][vc_single_image image="22654" img_size="large" alignment="center"][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Empowerment of families and fair trade', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'empowerment-of-families-and-fair-trade', '', '', '2016-06-17 09:08:21', '2016-06-17 14:08:21', '', 22509, 'http://localhost/evea/?page_id=22511', 0, 'page', '', 0),
